div.p:
—The long-standing U.S. policy of support for
                    Yugoslavia’s independence, territorial integrity and unity remains unchanged, as
                    does our understanding and respect for Yugoslavia’s nonaligned position;

—The measures we have taken are intended to respond to the seriousness of the
                    Soviet action. We are determined to maintain our sanctions until the Soviets
                    withdraw;

—But our response has left intact the framework of U.S.-Soviet relations, and we recognize the need to manage the
                    East-West relationship with dispassion and consistency. Specifically, we remain
                    firmly committed to further progress in arms control;

—The Soviets are aware that we would view any effort on their part to undermine
                    Yugoslavia’s independence, territorial integrity and unity with grave concern;
                    and

—We believe it is of extreme importance that all countries, especially major
                    nonaligned and Islamic states, cooperate with international efforts to make the
                    Soviets pay a heavy and continued price for their aggression;
